19/09/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- The EU will keep its doors open for Turkey following the next enlargement wave in 2007, German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder said Thursday (18 September). Depending on Turkey's performance, the Union will decide at the end of 2004 whether to commence accession negotiations.
In related developments, Turkish Labour and Social Security Minister Murat Basesgioglu said Thursday that his country was acting in accordance with the programme set forth by the European Council of Ministers regarding employment. According to Basesgioglu, the Turkish Labour Ministry's programme includes amendments to the individual and collective labour law, improvement of labour health and security, and social dialogue. Turkey is taking concrete and determined steps towards EU membership, the minister said. (Milliyet - 19/09/03; Anadolu Agency, TRT 2 - 18/09/03)
